, Sao Paulo, Horto Florestal, 1 ♂, 13.ii.1944, Ramalho col. (MZSP).

Terminalia (
Figs 7 D-F
): Tergite VI brown and segment VII+VIII brown to tawny with silver pruinosity. Surstyili in lateral view wide, more than 2 x the maximum cerci width; triangular shaped, slightly rounded at the apex. Surstyli in posterior view with small expansion laterally. Apex of the hypandrium directed backwards. Middle bar slightly shorter than total length of the granular structure of distiphallus. Apex of distiphallus curved.
